      <h1>Cluster Module - AI Lessons</h1>

      <h2>Module Design Patterns</h2>

      <div class="lesson">
        <div class="lesson-title">Modular Architecture for Map Features</div>
        <p>
          The Cluster Module demonstrates the importance of separating specialized functionality
          into dedicated modules. By isolating map clustering logic, we achieve:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Better code organization and maintainability</li>
          <li>Reduced coupling between components</li>
          <li>Ability to lazy-load map clustering functionality only when needed</li>
          <li>Easier testing of clustering features in isolation</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2>Integration Patterns</h2>

      <div class="lesson">
        <div class="lesson-title">Module Import Strategy</div>
        <p>When integrating specialized modules like the Cluster Module, it's important to:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Import only in components that need clustering functionality</li>
          <li>Consider lazy loading for performance optimization</li>
          <li>Maintain clear documentation of dependencies</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Example integration in a component:</p>
        <pre>
@Component({
  selector: 'app-map-with-clustering',
  templateUrl: './map-with-clustering.component.html',
  standalone: true,
  imports: [
    CommonModule,
    ClusterModule,
    // Other imports...
  ]
})
export class MapWithClusteringComponent {
  // Component implementation
}</pre
        >
      </div>

      <h2>Testing</h2>

      <div class="lesson">
        <div class="lesson-title">Testing Strategies for Map Modules</div>
        <p>When testing modules that interact with maps and clustering:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Mock external map services and APIs</li>
          <li>Test clustering algorithms with known data sets</li>
          <li>Verify performance with large marker sets</li>
          <li>Test edge cases like zero markers or extremely dense marker clusters</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h2>Dependencies</h2>

      <div class="lesson">
        <div class="lesson-title">Module Dependencies</div>
        <p>The Cluster Module has the following dependencies:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>@angular/core</strong> - Core Angular functionality</li>
          <li><strong>@angular/common</strong> - Common Angular directives and pipes</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Future implementations may include:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Map library integrations (Leaflet, Google Maps, etc.)</li>
          <li>Custom clustering algorithms</li>
        </ul>
